    "excerpt": "Breaking up is never easy, but it can be done with compassion and respect.",
    "content": "<h2>How to End a Relationship Kindly</h2><p>The kindest breakup is honest but not brutal. For relationships lasting more than a few months, break up in person. What to say: 'I've been thinking a lot about us, and I don't think we're right for each other long-term. I care about you, but I think we want different things.' Avoid: 'It's not you, it's me' (dismissive). After the breakup: respect their need for space, don't maintain constant contact, be clear about whether you want to remain friends.</p>",
