    "excerpt": "Dating anxiety is extremely common — and very manageable. Here are evidence-based strategies.",
    "content": "<h2>Dating Anxiety: Dating with Confidence</h2><p>Dating anxiety stems from fear of rejection, social anxiety, past trauma, or perfectionism. Cognitive reframing: challenge catastrophic thoughts with evidence. Practical strategies: choose familiar venues, prepare conversation topics, arrive early. During the date: focus on curiosity about the other person rather than worry about yourself. Remember the other person is probably nervous too. If anxiety significantly limits your dating, CBT is highly effective.</p>",
