    "excerpt": "Rejection is an inevitable part of dating. Here's how to process it healthily and maintain your confidence.",
    "content": "<h2>How to Handle Rejection in Dating</h2><p>Rejection activates the same brain regions as physical pain — it genuinely hurts. Reframing: every rejection is a data point, not a verdict. It tells you this specific person wasn't the right match — nothing about your worth. Practical response: allow yourself to feel disappointment briefly, then redirect attention to something positive. Don't ruminate. Build rejection resilience through exposure — the more you date, the less each individual rejection stings.</p>",
