    "excerpt": "Dating someone with anxiety requires patience, understanding, and specific strategies.",
    "content": "<h2>How to Date Someone with Anxiety</h2><p>Anxiety is a neurological condition, not a choice. Common manifestations: overthinking, seeking reassurance, avoidance, physical symptoms. What helps: consistency and reliability, validating feelings without reinforcing avoidance, learning their specific triggers. What doesn't help: telling them to 'just relax', accommodating all avoidance behaviors (which reinforces anxiety), taking their anxiety personally. Maintain your own wellbeing: keep your own social connections, set healthy boundaries, consider couples therapy if anxiety significantly affects the relationship.</p>",
