    "excerpt": "Much relationship advice for men misses the mark. Here's what research and women themselves say actually matters.",
    "content": "<h2>Relationship Advice for Men: What Women Actually Want</h2><p>Emotional availability is the most consistent finding in relationship research — being present, sharing vulnerabilities, responding empathetically. Consistency and reliability: doing what you say you'll do builds the trust relationships require. Active listening: shift from 'problem-solving listening' to 'empathetic listening' — women often want to be heard, not immediately fixed. Taking initiative: planning dates and being an engaged participant is consistently valued. Personal growth: men who are actively growing are consistently more attractive than men who are stagnant.</p>",
