    "content": "<h2>Are Dating App Subscriptions Worth It?</h2><p>Subscriptions are worth it when: the free tier is too limited (eHarmony, Match), premium features directly improve match quality (Hinge's Roses, Bumble's SuperSwipe), or you're actively dating and want efficiency. Not worth it when: you're not actively using the app, the free tier already gives you what you need (OkCupid), or you're paying for features you don't use. Best value: Hinge Premium ($9.99/mo annual). Best for serious relationships: eHarmony annual ($25.90/mo). Best free tier: OkCupid.</p>",
