    "content": "<h2>How to Maintain Attraction in a Long-Term Relationship</h2><p>Long-term couples who maintain strong attraction continue creating novel experiences together — activating the same reward pathways as early-stage romance. Pursue novel experiences together: new activities, travel, shared challenges. Maintain individual identity: your own interests, friendships, and personal growth make you more attractive to your partner. Physical intimacy requires intentional maintenance: schedule date nights, maintain non-sexual affection, communicate openly about intimate needs. Couples who prioritize physical intimacy report dramatically higher relationship satisfaction.</p>",
