    "excerpt": "Breakups are painful — but they're also opportunities for growth. Here's a comprehensive guide to healing.",
    "content": "<h2>The Complete Breakup Recovery Guide</h2><p>Breakup recovery follows grief stages: denial, anger, bargaining, depression, acceptance. The no-contact rule is the most consistently effective strategy — every contact reactivates neural pathways and resets healing. Allow yourself to feel the pain rather than suppressing it. Rebuild your individual identity: reconnect with neglected interests, friendships, and aspects of yourself that got lost in the relationship. Ready to date again when: you can think about your ex without intense pain, you're genuinely excited about meeting someone new, and you've extracted the lessons from the relationship.</p>",
