    "title": "Dating App Privacy and Security: How to Protect Your Data",
    "excerpt": "Dating apps collect enormous amounts of personal data. Here's how to protect your privacy.",
    "content": "<h2>Dating App Privacy and Security</h2><p>Dating apps collect: precise location, photos, conversations, behavioral data, device info, linked social media. Privacy settings to activate: disable precise location, review data sharing permissions, opt out of third-party data sharing, use a dedicated email address. Photo privacy: avoid photos revealing your home or workplace. Conversation privacy: assume conversations are not private — don't share sensitive personal information in app. Safest apps: eHarmony and Bumble have the strongest privacy policies among major dating apps.</p>",
    "author": "James Parker",
