    "excerpt": "Vulnerability is the foundation of genuine connection — but it requires courage and wisdom.",
    "content": "<h2>How to Be Vulnerable in Dating</h2><p>Vulnerability is sharing your authentic self in a context of appropriate trust — not oversharing on a first date or trauma dumping. The vulnerability gradient: early dates — share genuine opinions and light personal stories. As trust builds — share values and past experiences. In established relationships — share fears and deeper emotional content. Healthy vulnerability is reciprocal — if you're sharing and the other person consistently withholds, that's important information. Protect yourself by sharing gradually and observing how they respond to your openness.</p>",
