    "excerpt": "Getting over someone is one of the hardest emotional challenges. Here's what neuroscience and psychology say actually helps.",
    "content": "<h2>How to Get Over Someone: The Science-Based Guide</h2><p>Your brain processes romantic rejection like physical pain and goes through withdrawal similar to addiction. What helps: no contact (most effective — every contact reactivates neural pathways), cognitive reappraisal (focusing on incompatibilities rather than idealized memories), exercise (one of the most effective mood regulators), social connection (time with supportive friends accelerates healing). What doesn't help: social media stalking, premature rebound relationships, suppressing feelings, isolating yourself. Acute pain typically peaks at 2-3 weeks and significantly diminishes by 3 months.</p>",
