    "content": "<h2>Interracial Dating in 2026</h2><p>Interracial marriages have grown steadily — now representing 19% of new marriages in the U.S. Online dating has been a significant driver of this trend by expanding the pool of potential partners beyond immediate social circles. Best apps: eHarmony and OkCupid have the most diverse user bases and the strongest compatibility-based matching that transcends racial preferences. Challenges: family disapproval, cultural differences, and social pressure remain real factors. Success tips: communicate openly about cultural backgrounds and family dynamics early, find shared values that transcend cultural differences, build a support network of people who celebrate your relationship.</p>",
