    "excerpt": "Boundaries are the foundation of healthy relationships. Here's how to set and maintain them effectively.",
    "content": "<h2>Setting Healthy Boundaries in Dating: A 2026 Guide</h2><p>Healthy boundaries are not walls — they're guidelines that protect your wellbeing while allowing genuine connection. Types of boundaries: physical (comfort with touch and intimacy), emotional (what you share and when), time (how much time you invest), digital (social media and messaging expectations), and values (what you will and won't compromise on). How to set boundaries: know your limits before you need to enforce them, communicate them clearly and early, enforce them consistently. Red flags: someone who consistently pushes past your stated boundaries is showing you who they are. This pattern typically escalates rather than improves. Platforms like eHarmony attract users who are more likely to respect boundaries — the compatibility-focused approach filters for emotional maturity.</p>",
