    "content": "<h2>How to Build Emotional Intimacy</h2><p>Emotional intimacy develops through consistent vulnerability, active listening, and shared experiences. Key practices: ask deeper questions beyond surface small talk, share your own feelings and fears gradually, create rituals of connection (daily check-ins, weekly date nights), and respond empathetically when your partner shares. The four levels of emotional intimacy: sharing opinions, sharing feelings, sharing needs, and sharing fears and dreams. Most couples plateau at level 2 — consciously working toward levels 3 and 4 transforms relationships.</p>",
