    "excerpt": "The DTR conversation is one of the most important — and most avoided — conversations in dating.",
    "content": "<h2>How to Define the Relationship (DTR)</h2><p>The right time for the DTR talk: when you're genuinely interested in exclusivity, typically after 4-8 weeks of regular dating. How to start: 'I've really enjoyed spending time with you and I'd like to know where we stand.' Be direct about what you want: 'I'm looking for an exclusive relationship — is that something you're open to?' Accept the answer graciously. If they're not ready for exclusivity, you can decide whether to continue dating or move on. Avoid: ultimatums, having the conversation via text, and waiting so long that assumptions have formed.</p>",
